Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document with all the findings:

## Summary

I found the code related to the "New" badge in the prompt manager. Here's a comprehensive analysis of the bug and the relevant code:

### 1. Where the "New" Badge is Rendered

**Trigger Badge (on the main button):**
- `/Users/jessezhang/Desktop/Coding/side-projects/gemini-voyager/src/pages/content/prompt/index.ts` (line 426)
  - Class: `gv-pm-trigger-new` (added to the trigger button when `changelogBadgeActive` is true)
  - CSS styling in `/Users/jessezhang/Desktop/Coding/side-projects/gemini-voyager/public/contentStyle.css` (lines 860-886)
  - Shows "NEW" text with animation

**Version Number Badge (on the version text):**
- `/Users/jessezhang/Desktop/Coding/side-projects/gemini-voyager/src/pages/content/prompt/index.ts` (line 555)
  - Class: `gv-pm-version-outdated` (added to version badge when `changelogBadgeActive` is true)
  - CSS styling in `/Users/jessezhang/Desktop/Coding/side-projects/gemini-voyager/public/contentStyle.css` (lines 1187-1221)
  - Shows "NEW" text with animation

Both badges are pseudo-elements (`::after`) with `content: 'NEW'`

### 2. How the Click Handler is Supposed to Dismiss It

**On Trigger Click** (lines 1143-1172 in prompt/index.ts):
```typescript
trigger.addEventListener('click', async () => {
  // When changelog badge is active, open changelog modal instead
  if (changelogBadgeActive) {
    changelogBadgeActive = false;
    trigger.classList.remove('gv-pm-trigger-new');
    try {
      await showChangelogModalDirect();
    } catch {
      // Ignore errors
    }
    // Hide trigger if PM was hidden by user
    if (pmHiddenByUser) {
      trigger.style.display = 'none';
    }
    return;
  }
  // ... normal prompt manager click logic
});
```

**On Version Badge Click** (lines 528-551 in prompt/index.ts):
```typescript
versionBadge.addEventListener('click', async (e) => {
  e.stopPropagation();
  closePanel();
  // If badge was active, clear it
  if (changelogBadgeActive) {
    changelogBadgeActive = false;
    trigger.classList.remove('gv-pm-trigger-new');
    versionBadge.classList.remove('gv-pm-version-outdated');
    try {
      await showChangelogModalDirect();
    } catch {
      // Ignore
    }
    if (pmHiddenByUser) {
      trigger.style.display = 'none';
    }
  } else {
    try {
      await openChangelog();
    } catch {
      // Ignore
    }
  }
});
```

### 3. How the "Seen" State is Persisted

The "seen" state is managed via Chrome's storage API with these key components:

**Storage Key:**
- `gvChangelogDismissedVersion` (defined in `/Users/jessezhang/Desktop/Coding/side-projects/gemini-voyager/src/core/types/common.ts` line 97)

**Marking as Dismissed:**
- Location: `/Users/jessezhang/Desktop/Coding/side-projects/gemini-voyager/src/pages/content/changelog/index.ts` (lines 550-553)
```typescript
await chrome.storage.local.set({
  [StorageKeys.CHANGELOG_DISMISSED_VERSION]: EXTENSION_VERSION,
});
```

**Checking if Unread:**
- Location: `/Users/jessezhang/Desktop/Coding/side-projects/gemini-voyager/src/pages/content/changelog/index.ts` (lines 575-583)
```typescript
export async function hasUnreadChangelog(): Promise<boolean> {
  try {
    const result = await chrome.storage.local.get(StorageKeys.CHANGELOG_DISMISSED_VERSION);
    const dismissed = result[StorageKeys.CHANGELOG_DISMISSED_VERSION] as string | undefined;
    return dismissed !== EXTENSION_VERSION;
  } catch {
    return false;
  }
}
```

**Badge Activation Logic:**
- Location: `/Users/jessezhang/Desktop/Coding/side-projects/gemini-voyager/src/pages/content/prompt/index.ts` (lines 322-329)
```typescript
// Check changelog badge mode
try {
  const [modeRes, unread] = await Promise.all([
    browser.storage.local.get(StorageKeys.CHANGELOG_NOTIFY_MODE),
    hasUnreadChangelog(),
  ]);
  const notifyMode = modeRes?.[StorageKeys.CHANGELOG_NOTIFY_MODE];
  changelogBadgeActive = notifyMode === 'badge' && unread;
} catch {
  // Ignore errors
}
```

### The Bug

The issue is that clicking the badge should dismiss it by:
1. Setting `changelogBadgeActive = false` (local variable)
2. Removing the CSS classes (`gv-pm-trigger-new`, `gv-pm-version-outdated`)
3. **However**, these changes are only in-memory. The actual dismissal is only persisted through `showChangelogModalDirect()` → `showChangelogModal()` which sets `CHANGELOG_DISMISSED_VERSION` in storage.

If `showChangelogModalDirect()` fails or throws an error (caught silently), the version won't be marked as dismissed in storage, so on page reload, `hasUnreadChangelog()` will still return `true`, and the badge will re-appear.

